<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-01-13T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-01-13T19:00:00-05:00" n="60" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d60">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/5749a: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Minister in China (<persName type="to">Johnson</persName>)</hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-01-13T19:00:00-05:00">January 13, 1933—7
                                p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>13. Please report the date and the important provisions of any agreement
                            now in effect between the Boxer Protocol powers in reference to
                            occupation by them of points listed in Boxer Protocol, Article 9,
                            indicating what points may, according to any such agreement, be occupied
                            by each power. If necessary, consult Tientsin.</p>
                        <p>Department is giving consideration to your telegrams relating to problems
                            in this connection.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>